Justice Department says it will keep investigating Michael Brown's death
The Obama administration will continue investigating the death of black teenager Michael Brown, attorney general Eric Holder said in a statement late Monday. The statement followed news earlier in the evening that a grand jury would not indict police officer Darren Wilson in Brown's death. Politico's Jen EpsteinÂ  a photo of the full Holder statement which is below.   
